div.p: RACHEL: I can't tell you my first, but I can remember being probably around 14 years old, with some kids who were older than I at a party and we were drinking...
RACHEL: And I remember drinking and I remember there was a cute boy there, and again I was 13, 14, 13 maybe...
RACHEL: I remember that night, I remember talking to this person, and then I remember this craziness of people opening a car door and dragging me out of the back of a car...

RACHEL: Somehow, between the time I had started drinking and when the car door opened, I had gotten drunk, I had gone off with a boy older than I, and ended up in a backseat of a car, in an incredibly vulnerable position.

RACHEL: And I don't remember what happened in between there. But it didn't scare me! What's wrong with that, you know? And I actually had forgotten completely about that until just recently. I remembered that situation.
